article.headline: Freshman Harmon nearly perfect in No. 16 Stanford's win
article.linkText: Freshman Harmon nearly perfect in No. 16 Stanford's win
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Devanei Hampton had 21 points and three
rebounds to help California to a 71-50 win against Oregon State at
Gill Coliseum on Saturday afternoon.

Ashley Walker added 14 points and 15 rebounds for the Golden
Bears, who improved to 12-4 overall and 4-2 in the Pacific-10
Conference.

Kim Butler and Karen Vickery scored 16 and 14 points,
respectively, for Oregon State (6-6, 0-4).

Hampton, a freshman post, scored the last four points of an 11-2
Cal run that gave the Golden Bears a 48-30 lead with 14:35
remaining in the game. Oregon State got no closer the rest of the
way.

Cal, which started four freshmen, used an 11-0 run to break open
a close game in the first half.But Oregon State scored 11 of the
final 13 points of the half to cut the Golden Bears' lead to 33-23
at halftime.

Walker, a freshman post, secured her third straight
double-double and third of the season by halftime with 10 points
and 10 rebounds.

California bettered its win total from last season with the
victory. Oregon State has tied its win total from last season.

Oregon State, which lost its fifth straight game, had its lowest
scoring game of the season.

California was coming off its lowest scoring output of the
season in a 70-41 loss at Oregon on Thursday. The Golden Bears have
won eight of their last 10.
